{
  "texts": [
    "It has to be stressed, however, that other solutions could have emerged and could still be imagined for each of the domains.",
    "Co-creation is increasingly regarded as a major success factor for digital health and artificial intelligence.",
    "Carusi et al., for instance, pointed out that development and adoption of medical AI is \"as much societal as it is technological\" 26, stressing the need for collaboration between experts to address transparency and build trust.",
    "In contrast to our inclusive co-creation concept, however, this approach does not envisage active involvement of wider society or regulators in medical AI development.",
    "Beyond only providing one-directional user-feedback, co-creation calls for stakeholders' active participation throughout the innovation cycle."
  ]
}